{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"owner","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Node","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"text":"? { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want a child to be persisted to a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", you must set "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/owner","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" in addition to calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"addChild(node:forceReadableName:`internal`:)"},{"text":". This is typically relevant for ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tool scripts"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"text":"editor plugins","type":"text"},{"text":". If a new node is added to the tree without setting its owner as an ancestor in that tree, it will be visible in the 2D\/3D view, but not in the scene tree (and not persisted when packing or saving).","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node\/owner"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The node owner. A node can have any ancestor node as owner (i.e. a parent, grandparent, etc. node ascending in the tree). This implies that ","type":"text"},{"code":"addChild(node:forceReadableName:`internal`:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" should be called before setting the owner, so that this relationship of parenting exists. When saving a node (using ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"), all the nodes it owns will be saved with it. This allows for the creation of complex scene trees, with instancing and subinstancing.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC5ownerACSgvp","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"title":"owner","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"owner"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Node","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/owner"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","abstract":[{"text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Node","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node","title":"Node","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Node"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Base class for all scene objects."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node/owner":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/owner","abstract":[{"text":"The node owner. A node can have any ancestor node as owner (i.e. a parent, grandparent, etc. node ascending in the tree). This implies that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"addChild(node:forceReadableName:`internal`:)"},{"type":"text","text":" should be called before setting the owner, so that this relationship of parenting exists. When saving a node (using "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"), all the nodes it owns will be saved with it. This allows for the creation of complex scene trees, with instancing and subinstancing.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"owner"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Node","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node\/owner","title":"owner"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/PackedScene":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/packedscene","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PackedScene"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PackedScene","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An abstraction of a serialized scene."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene","title":"PackedScene","kind":"symbol"}}}